HEADWORD: Umlauted
<hw>Um"laut*ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>Having the
umlaut; <as>as, <ex>umlauted</ex> vowels</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no natural connection between <qex>umlauted</qex> forms
and plurality.</q> <rj><qau>Earle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umpirage</ent>⟦br⟧
